    <form id="form1" runat="server">
    <div style="font-size: 15px; margin-left:50px; width:90%">
    <br /><br /><br />
    <p style="text-align:center; font-size: large; color: #0000FF; font-weight: bold;">INSTRUCTIONS TO FILL UP THE CONVOCATION REGISTRATION FORM</p>
       
    
<br />
Click on the link ‘6th Convocation Registration’ on the home page of Eastern University website (www.easternuni.edu.bd) or copy paste the following link in your web browser:


 <a href="http://webportal.easternuni.edu.bd/Convocation/_ConvChkInfo.aspx" style="font-weight: bold; color: blue; ">http://webportal.easternuni.edu.bd/Convocation/_ConvChkInfo.aspx</a>
<br /><br />

1. Enter your <strong style="text-decoration: underline">Student ID.</strong><br /><br />

2. Choose <strong style="text-decoration: underline">Faculty</strong> from the drop down list (Arts, Business Administration, Engineering & Technology, or Law).
<br /><br />
3. Enter your <strong style="text-decoration: underline">CGPA</strong> (up to two decimal points e.g. 3.65).
<br /><br />
4. Enter last <strong style="text-decoration: underline">registered year</strong>,
        and choose the <strong style="text-decoration: underline">semester</strong> from the drop down list (e.g. if you have completed all requirements for graduation in Spring 2017, type ‘2017’ in the last registered year and choose ‘Spring’ from the semester drop down menu).
<br /><br />

5. Click the <strong>‘submit’</strong> button and <strong style="color: #ff0000">WAIT</strong>.
        You will be taken to the ‘Registration Form’.
<br /><br />

6. Check your <strong style="text-decoration: underline">name, e-mail, contact</strong>
        (11 digit mobile number*), <strong style="text-decoration: underline">mailing address</strong>.
        Update e-mail, contact number, mailing address (if needed). Please note that communication will be made using your contact number and e-mail mentioned in the form. So, be accurate in entering this information.
<br />

* If the number shows like 8801552XXXXXX, make it 01552XXXXXX
<br /><br />

N.B.: If there is a mismatch in your name, and/or academic information, please contact the Registrar’s Office at the earliest to make necessary corrections.
<br /><br />

7. Enter your <strong>employment status</strong> (if applicable), filling in the required fields.
        <br />
<br />

8. <strong style="color: #0000ff">If you wish to bring a guest along with you (guardian/parent) in the convocation, please mention the name of the guest, relationship with the guest, contact number of the guest, and address of the guest.
</strong>

<br /><br />

9. Click the <strong>‘Submit’</strong> button and <strong style="color: #ff0000">WAIT</strong>.
        You will be taken to the <strong>‘payment page’</strong>.
<br /><br />

10. If you wish to pay online, click the <strong>‘pay now’</strong> button. You will be taken to the online payment options. Choose the payment option; the system will mention the amount to be paid. 
<br /><br />

11. (a) Follow the payment instructions. Upon successful payment of the amount, you will get a success notification. You will receive a payment confirmation notice in your e-mail. <strong>Your registration is now complete!</strong>
<br /><br />

11. (b) Pay the registration fee in Bank (Any branch of DHAKA BANK, Dhanmondi Branch of IFIC Bank, and Dhanmondi Branch of UCBL) using EU payment slip.

 Students paying the registration fee offline i.e. in the bank should click the ‘<strong>Check Payment</strong>’
        button 2 (two) working days after making the payment.
 
 <p style="font-size: 10px; color:Black">e.g. if you make the payment on Monday, check the registration status (i.e. click the ‘<strong>check payment</strong>’ button) on Wednesday to know about your registration status. If you pay on Thursday, check your status on Sunday (Friday and Saturday are bank holidays).
 </p>
        Then
 
  you will get a success notification. <b>Your registration is now complete!</b>  
        <br />
        <br />
